<problem display_name="Has Many Associations" rerandomize="never">
  <startouttext/>
  <p>In the previous example using <span style="color: #66C; font-size:larger;"><tt>has_many :through</tt></span>, can we say <span style="color: #66C; font-size:larger;"><tt>@user.movies &lt;&lt; movie</tt></span>?</p>
  <endouttext/>
  <choiceresponse>
    <radiogroup>
      <choice correct="false">
        <text>
          <span style="color: #F90;"> Yes, since it quacks like a collection </span>
        </text>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="false">
        <text>
          <span style="color: #063;"> Yes, since <span style="color: #66C; font-size:larger;"><tt>user</tt></span> is the "owning" side of the association</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="false">
        <text>
          <span style="color: #C00;"> Yes, as long as the <span style="color: #66C; font-size:larger;"><tt>movies</tt></span> table has a <span style="color: #66C; font-size:larger;"><tt>user_id</tt></span> field</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="true">
        <text>
          <span style="color:#006;"> No</span>
        </text>
      </choice>
    </radiogroup>
  </choiceresponse>
</problem>
